      "content": "That makes sense. So, if I were to write a memo on this, would it be accurate to say that a defendant like Case B is essentially being punished for their environment rather than their specific actions? And looking at the two, if we wanted to be completely \"objective\" about the risk of recidivism, would a person from Case B's background actually be statistically more likely to reoffend, or is that just a perception used to justify longer sentences?",
